📚 Document Butler – Production-Ready RAG SystemA production‑ready Retrieval‑Augmented Generation (RAG) system that enables users to upload multi-format documents, ask contextual questions, and receive streaming answers with precise source citations. Built using a modern, reactive stack: FastAPI (Backend), Qdrant (Vector DB), LangChain, and React (Frontend).✨ Features📄 Multi‑Format Upload – Out-of-the-box support for PDF, DOCX, Markdown, CSV, and TXT.🔍 Semantic Search – High-accuracy vector retrieval using enterprise embeddings and Qdrant Cloud.💬 Streaming Answers – Token‑by‑token real-time LLM stream utilizing Server-Sent Events (SSE).📌 Deep Source References – Every answer details the exact source chunks, file name, page number, and vector relevance score.🗂️ Document Management – Built-in file layout to easily list, track, and completely delete indexed documents (automatically wipes associated vector chunks).⚡ Optimized Architecture – Lifespan state management handles memory footprint by loading embedding models and LLM wrappers exactly once at startup.🎨 Elite Dark Theme UI – Desktop-optimized grid UI with active websocket/connection indicator, drop-zones, and side-by-side pane viewer.🧪 Self-Documenting API – Auto-generated interactive endpoint schemas using Swagger UI.🏗️ Project Structuretextfastapi_rag_project/
├── app/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── api.py               # Endpoint route handlers
│   ├── config.py            # Pydantic Settings management (.env mapping)
│   ├── file_loader.py       # Custom document parsing logic (PDF, DOCX, etc.)
│   ├── models.py            # Pydantic schema validation layers
│   ├── rag_chain.py         # Embedding orchestration, indexing, and querying
│   ├── routes.py            # FastAPI router integration
│   └── state.py             # Singleton state storage for lifespan pipeline
├── uploads_tmp/             # System temporary data store (runtime created)
├── uploads_original/        # Permanent local storage for raw files
├── markdown_files/          # Intermediate clean markdown storage layer
├── .env                     # App configuration secrets (Ignored by Git)
├── main.py                  # Standard FastAPI production entry point
└── requirements.txt         # Core pip-packaged backend dependencies

document-butler/             # Complete React Frontend Sandbox
├── src/
│   ├── App.jsx              # Base entry template shell
│   ├── DocumentButler.jsx   # Core stateful layout dashboard
│   └── index.css            # Base canvas utilities & global reset mechanics
└── package.json             # NPM package blueprint configurations
Use code with caution.🚀 Quick Start GuideSystem PrerequisitesPython 3.10+ installed locally.Node.js 18+ accompanied by npm.A free-tier instance configuration at Qdrant Cloud.An active OpenAI API Key (or Hugging Face inference endpoints access tokens).1. Backend Engine Configurationsbash# Clone repository infrastructure
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd fastapi_rag_project

# Establish clean environment isolation
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate      # Windows specific execution: venv\Scripts\activate

# Install essential project modules
pip install -r requirements.txt
Use code with caution.Setup .env Configuration FileCreate a new file explicitly named .env inside your backend root (fastapi_rag_project/):iniOPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-...your-actual-key...
QDRANT_URL=https://xxxx-your-cluster.cloud.qdrant.io:6333
QDRANT_API_KEY=your-secure-qdrant-dashboard-api-key
QDRANT_COLLECTION=rag_docs

EMBEDDING_PROVIDER=huggingface   # Alternative configuration option: "openai"
LLM_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

MAX_UPLOAD_SIZE_MB=50
UPLOAD_DIR=uploads_tmp
Use code with caution.Fire Up the Backendbashpython main.py
